# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Regenerative Microclimate Probe, API keys
#  THIS is the file where you enter your keys.
#    cp .env.example .env      then fill in the values below.
#  .env is gitignored, it is never committed and never sent to the browser
#  (the FastAPI backend reads it server-side). Treat every value as a password.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# 1) infrared.city, REQUIRED for all SDK runs (UTCI / wind / solar).
#    Get it: log in at https://infrared.city  →  account dashboard → API keys.
INFRARED_API_KEY=

# 2) Roboflow, tree / canopy detection from aerial imagery (Tier 3 CV).
#    Get it: https://roboflow.com → sign up (free) → your Workspace →
#            Settings → API Keys → copy (or "Generate New Key").
#    Also set the model (project/version). A live-verified public canopy model:
#    "detecting-tree-canopy/1" (class "tree-canopy"). Browse universe.roboflow.com.
ROBOFLOW_API_KEY=
ROBOFLOW_MODEL=detecting-tree-canopy/1

# 3) Copernicus Data Space Ecosystem / Sentinel Hub, Sentinel-2 NDVI (Tier 2 EO).
#    Get it: register at https://dataspace.copernicus.eu → Sentinel Hub Dashboard →
#            User Settings → OAuth clients → Create → copy Client ID + Secret
#            (the secret is shown once, save it now).
SH_CLIENT_ID=
SH_CLIENT_SECRET=

# 4) GUS.earth (gAIa): urban-forest tree intelligence / growth models.
#    Get it: https://gus.earth (app: https://gaia.gus.earth) → sign up / request access.
#    API base https://backend.gus.earth ; key goes in the X-API-Key header ;
#    trees at /api/v1/gus/trees with a lnglatbounds query. Docs: /docs
GUS_API_KEY=

# ── Optional ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Silence the SDK's first-run agent hint log line.
# INFRARED_QUIET=1
# Override the GUS API base if needed.
# GUS_API_BASE=https://backend.gus.earth

# NOTE: ESA WorldCover land-cover (used by the tool's ecology readout + map
# overlay) and the city open-data connectors (Rome / Marseille / Cork) are
# KEYLESS, they need no entry here.
